olitics of burial long associated with Antigone relevant for theorizing militant forms of mourning in the global south. Grounded in settler colonial critique, black and woman of color feminisms, and queer and trans of color critique, Antigone in the Americas offers a more radical interpretation of Antigone, one relevant to subjects situated under multiple and interlocking systems of oppression.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aDeath in literature. 0aDemocracy in literature. 0aGreek drama (Tragedy)xHistory and criticism. 0aSex in literature. 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLatin American, Caribbean, and Latinx Studies : Latin American Studies. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Theory. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848429740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438484297423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438484297/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles